      "question": "What problem is multi-head attention designed to address compared with a single attention head?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "A single head forces one average pattern of relevance instead of letting the model look in different places for different reasons",
        "A single head cannot be run on GPUs",
        "A single head cannot use softmax normalization",
        "A single head always ignores nearby words"
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "Different linguistic or semantic relations may require attending to different tokens. Multi-head attention gives the model several independent attention mechanisms instead of one blended pattern.",
